description._content: Description: 27. Showing Eucalyptus plants established and thriving on the bed of the Fresh Water Lake. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: 28. Showing area of the Fresh Water Lake successfully reclaimed by Eucalyptus which are now well established after about 10 years. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives. Feel free to share it within the spirit of the Commons Please use the comments section below the pictures to share any information you have about the people, places or events shown.
